The paper discusses image captioning, which is a problem that lies at the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also explores different decoders and attentional models popular in neural machine translation, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, since the paper deals with generating textual descriptions of images, it could also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
